50|$|In the {{conflict}} of laws, <b>lex</b> <b>loci</b> actus is the law of thelace where the act occurred {{that gave rise to}} the legal claim. This is often confused with <b>lex</b> <b>loci</b> delicti commissi which is where the tort is committed. While typically they both point to the same location, in the case of product liability, for example, the <b>lex</b> <b>loci</b> actus would be the place of manufacturing, while the <b>lex</b> <b>loci</b> delicti commissi would be the place of injury.|$|R
